cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.PF 

This paper discusses the performance characteristics of a 3D-stacked memory, specifically the Hybrid Memory Cube (HMC), which utilizes a network-on-chip (NoC) for internal connectivity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AR (Architecture), which deals with the design and analysis of computer systems and architectures. The paper also discusses the implications of NoC integration on system- and software-level designs, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of NoCs also involves electronic components and circuits, which could fall under cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.PF (Performance).
